The board shall issue an esthetician license to any person who:
Is of good moral character and temperate habit;
Is at least eighteen (18) years of age;
Has a high school diploma, General Educational Development (GED) diploma, or the results from the Test for Adult Basic Education indicating a score equivalent to the twelfth grade of high school;
Has satisfactorily completed one thousand (1,000) hours of instruction in a licensed school approved by the board;
Has received a satisfactory grade on an examination prescribed by the board to determine fitness to practice as an esthetician; and
Has paid a fee of at least seventy-five dollars ($75) to be adjusted as needed in administrative regulations promulgated by the board.

The board shall issue a license to teach esthetic practices to any person who:
Is of good moral character and temperate habit;
Is at least eighteen (18) years of age;
Has a high school diploma, General Educational Development (GED) diploma, or the results from the Test for Adult Basic Education indicating a score equivalent to the twelfth grade of high school;
Holds a current cosmetologist and instructor's license;
Has completed fifty (50) hours in esthetics training within the last two (2) years;
Has received a satisfactory grade on the examination for the teaching of esthetics as prescribed by the board; and
Has paid a fee promulgated by the board in administrative regulations.
